│ Field                    │ Value                                                                                     │
├──────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ patch_type               │ full                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ multiwindow_motionclip_with_handcrafted_gait_features                                     │
│ patch_description        │ Key insights from analyzing the baseline:                                                 │
│                          │ 1. Class 2 (severe PD) gets F1=0.00 - the model never predicts it. This is the biggest    │
│                          │ issue.                                                                                    │
│                          │ 2. Single center-crop of 60 frames loses temporal information about gait variability.     │
│                          │ 3. The MLP classifier with FocalLoss isn't handling the class imbalance well enough.      │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ Novel approach:                                                                           │
│                          │ 1. Multi-window MotionCLIP features: Slide multiple 60-frame windows across each walk,    │
│                          │ extract 512-dim embeddings per window, then compute mean, std, min, max statistics across │
│                          │ windows. This captures gait variability and consistency - key PD indicators.              │
│                          │ 2. Handcrafted gait features: Extract physics-informed features including joint angular   │
│                          │ velocities, left-right asymmetry (critical PD marker), stride regularity via              │
│                          │ autocorrelation, and frequency-domain features from hip/knee joints.                      │
│                          │ 3. Combined feature vector fed to a gradient-boosted ensemble (XGBoost-style via sklearn) │
│                          │ with strong class weighting, plus an MLP ensemble with aggressive oversampling of class   │
│                          │ 2.                                                                                        │
│                          │ 4. Explicit class-weight balancing with sqrt-inverse-frequency weighting and SMOTE-like   │
│                          │ oversampling of minority class during training.                                           │
│                          │ 5. Temperature-scaled predictions with a bias toward class 2 to fix the zero-prediction   │
│                          │ problem.                                                                                  │
│ num_applied              │ 1                                                                                         │
│ api_costs                │ $0.2823                                                                                   │
