│ Field                    │ Value                                                                                     │
├──────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ patch_type               │ full                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ motionclip_aggregated                                                                     │
│ patch_description        │ Completely restructures the program to use a multi-window temporal aggregation strategy   │
│                          │ with MotionCLIP. Instead of extracting a single 60-frame center crop per walk, we slide a │
│                          │ 60-frame window across each walk with 50% overlap and extract MotionCLIP features from    │
│                          │ each window. These features are then temporally pooled using learnable attention weights  │
│                          │ to produce a single walk-level embedding. This captures more temporal information from    │
│                          │ long walking bouts while maintaining the benefits of pretrained MotionCLIP features.      │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ Key architectural changes:                                                                │
│                          │ 1. Multi-window feature extraction instead of single center crop                          │
│                          │ 2. Attention-based temporal pooling with learnable weights                                │
│                          │ 3. Integrated end-to-end training (no separate feature extraction phase)                  │
│                          │ 4. Proper handling of variable-length sequences through padding and masking               │
│                          │ 5. Use of official CARE-PD utilities instead of inlined implementations                   │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This structure better captures gait patterns across entire walks, especially important    │
│                          │ for longer sequences, and gives the model attention mechanisms to focus on the most       │
│                          │ discriminative temporal segments.                                                         │
