│ Field                    │ Value                                                                                     │
├──────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ patch_type               │ diff                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ multi_window_attention_pooling                                                            │
│ patch_description        │ The current implementation uses a single center-cropped 60-frame window per walk to feed  │
│                          │ into MotionCLIP, discarding most of the temporal information in longer sequences (some    │
│                          │ walks have >3000 frames). This leads to severe information loss, especially for longer    │
│                          │ gait cycles.                                                                              │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ I propose replacing the single crop with a multi-window approach: slide a 60-frame window │
│                          │ across each walk with 50% overlap, extract MotionCLIP features for each window, then      │
│                          │ apply attention-based temporal pooling to aggregate these window features into a single   │
│                          │ walk-level embedding.                                                                     │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This preserves more gait dynamics and allows the model to focus on the most               │
│                          │ discriminative temporal segments. The attention pooling learns to weight informative      │
│                          │ windows (e.g., stride phases) higher than less informative ones.                          │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ Key changes:                                                                              │
│                          │ 1. Modify extract_features() to use sliding windows with attention pooling                │
│                          │ 2. Add LearnableTemporalAttentionPool module for weighted aggregation                     │
│                          │ 3. Keep MotionCLIP encoder frozen as before                                               │
│                          │ 4. Update train_and_predict() to handle variable number of windows per walk               │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This approach better handles variable-length sequences and captures more gait cycle       │
│                          │ information, which should particularly improve detection of severe PD (class 2) where     │
│                          │ gait abnormalities may appear intermittently.                                             │
│ num_applied              │ 2                                                                                         │
