╭──────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Field                    │ Value                                                                                     │
├──────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ patch_type               │ diff                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ multi_window_attention_pooling                                                            │
│ patch_description        │ Current feature extraction uses a single center-cropped 60-frame window, discarding most  │
│                          │ temporal information in longer sequences (up to 3015 frames). This is highly suboptimal   │
│                          │ for gait analysis where rhythmic patterns and asymmetries are distributed across time.    │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ I propose to replace the single crop with multi-window attention pooling:                 │
│                          │ - Slide a 60-frame window across each sequence with 50% overlap                           │
│                          │ - Extract MotionCLIP embedding for each window                                            │
│                          │ - Apply learnable attention pooling over all window embeddings to produce a single        │
│                          │ sequence-level representation                                                             │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This preserves temporal structure, captures multiple gait cycles, and allows the model to │
│                          │ focus on most discriminative phases (e.g., stance vs swing). Attention pooling is         │
│                          │ differentiable and handles variable numbers of windows naturally.                         │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ The change requires modifying extract_features() to implement sliding windows and         │
│                          │ attention pooling, and updating ClassifierMLP to handle the same input dimension (still   │
│                          │ 512-dim).                                                                                 │
│ num_applied              │ 1                                                                                         │
│ api_costs                │ $0.0026                                                                                   │
│ error_attempt            │ None                                                                                      │
