│ patch_type               │ diff                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ fix_class_weights_and_improve_classifier                                                  │
│ patch_description        │ The critical bug: class weights `w` are computed (inverse frequency) but never passed to  │
│                          │ FocalLoss, which uses a scalar alpha=0.25 treating all classes equally. This causes class │
│                          │ 2 (severe PD, fewest samples) to get F1=0.00.                                             │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ Fix: Replace FocalLoss with nn.CrossEntropyLoss(weight=w) to properly upweight the        │
│                          │ minority class. Also:                                                                     │
│                          │ 1. Increase epochs to 300 for better convergence with weighted loss                       │
│                          │ 2. Add label smoothing to reduce overconfidence on majority classes                       │
│                          │ 3. Use a deeper MLP with batch norm for better feature learning                           │
│                          │ 4. Add oversampling of minority class during training batches                             │
