│ patch_type               │ diff                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ fix_weighted_loss_bug                                                                     │
│ patch_description        │ The current code calculates class weights `w` but never passes them to the loss function. │
│                          │ The FocalLoss is using fixed alpha=0.25 instead of the computed per-class weights. This   │
│                          │ is a critical bug that prevents recovery of class 2 (severe PD) which requires higher     │
│                          │ loss weight. We must fix this by either modifying FocalLoss to accept the computed        │
│                          │ weights or switching to CrossEntropyLoss with weight argument.                            │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This fix directly addresses the primary bottleneck: class 2 recall is 0.00 across all     │
│                          │ versions due to this weighting bug. The computed weights will boost the gradient          │
│                          │ contribution from class 2 samples (weight ~1.59) while reducing class 0 contribution      │
│                          │ (weight ~0.68), forcing the model to pay attention to severe PD cases.                    │
