│ patch_type               │ full                                                                                      │
│ patch_name               │ hybrid_features_sklearn_ensemble                                                          │
│ patch_description        │ This new approach fundamentally shifts from neural network-based classification to a      │
│                          │ hybrid feature engineering + sklearn ensemble strategy, directly addressing the key       │
│                          │ insights from the analysis:                                                               │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 1. **Primary Architecture Change**: Instead of relying on MotionCLIP features with MLP    │
│                          │ classifier, we use comprehensive handcrafted gait features as the primary input,          │
│                          │ supplemented by MotionCLIP features only when available.                                  │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 2. **Feature Engineering**: Implements 9 categories of physics-informed gait features     │
│                          │ including joint statistics, velocity/acceleration, left-right asymmetry, range of motion, │
│                          │ stride frequency, gait regularity, and freeze-of-gait proxies - all critical for PD       │
│                          │ assessment.                                                                               │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 3. **Classifier Selection**: Uses sklearn's GradientBoostingClassifier with class         │
│                          │ weighting and explicit oversampling of class 2 (severe PD), which consistently            │
│                          │ outperforms neural networks on small, imbalanced datasets.                                │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 4. **Hybrid Features**: When MotionCLIP is available, combines handcrafted features with  │
│                          │ MotionCLIP embeddings using mean pooling (not attention) for stable, reproducible         │
│                          │ results.                                                                                  │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 5. **Critical Fixes**:                                                                    │
│                          │    - Replaces FocalLoss with proper class-weighted CrossEntropyLoss                       │
│                          │    - Uses mean pooling instead of random attention pooling                                │
│                          │    - Implements proper class imbalance handling through oversampling                      │
│                          │    - Provides robust handling of variable sequence lengths                                │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ This approach directly addresses why the previous best (0.41) was 27% below the           │
│                          │ RandomForest baseline (0.565) - by making handcrafted features the primary approach       │
│                          │ rather than relying on MotionCLIP alone.                                                  │
