│ patch_type               │ cross                                                                                     │
│ patch_name               │ hybrid_features_sklearn_ensemble                                                          │
│ patch_description        │ Based on analysis of the best-performing programs, the key insights are:                  │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ 1. MotionCLIP features alone achieve only 0.41 macro-F1 - 27% below the RandomForest      │
│                          │ baseline (0.565)                                                                          │
│                          │ 2. The random attention pooling used in some programs is harmful; mean pooling is more    │
│                          │ reliable                                                                                  │
│                          │ 3. The best approach combines handcrafted gait features with MotionCLIP embeddings        │
│                          │ 4. Sklearn classifiers (RandomForest, GradientBoosting, SVM) outperform MLPs on this      │
│                          │ small dataset                                                                             │
│                          │ 5. Class 2 (severe PD) performance is critical and requires explicit handling through     │
│                          │ class_weight='balanced'                                                                   │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ The new approach makes handcrafted features the primary method, combines them with        │
│                          │ MotionCLIP when available, and uses sklearn ensemble classifiers that handle class        │
│                          │ imbalance properly. This addresses the fundamental flaw in previous approaches that       │
│                          │ relied too heavily on MotionCLIP features while using suboptimal MLP classifiers.         │
│                          │                                                                                           │
│                          │ Key changes:                                                                              │
│                          │ - Extract comprehensive handcrafted gait features as primary approach                     │
│                          │ - Use sklearn classifiers with class_weight='balanced' instead of MLP                     │
│                          │ - Combine with MotionCLIP features via concatenation when available                       │
│                          │ - Use simple mean pooling instead of attention pooling                                    │
│                          │ - Handle class imbalance through both class_weight and optional oversampling              │
